Netflix Data Analysis Project Report
1. Project Overview

This project analyzes Netflix’s movies and TV shows dataset to uncover trends and insights about audience preferences, ratings, genres, release years, and global distribution. The goal is to understand which content performs best, how viewership varies across countries, and to provide actionable insights for content strategy.

2. Dataset
Source: Netflix dataset (netflix_titles.csv)
Number of records: ~8,000 movies and TV shows
Columns include:
show_id – Unique ID
type – Movie / TV Show
title – Name of the show
director – Director’s name
cast – Main actors
country – Country of production
date_added – Added on Netflix
release_year – Year of release
rating – Audience rating
duration – Duration in minutes / seasons
listed_in – Genre
3. Tools Used
Python – Data cleaning, analysis, and visualization (Pandas, Matplotlib, Seaborn)
Power BI – Interactive dashboards and visual analytics
Jupyter Notebook – For step-by-step analysis and insights
4. Methodology
Data Cleaning
Handle missing values and duplicates
Standardize genre and country fields
Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA)
Analyze distribution of content by type, genre, country, and year
Study rating trends across content types
Visualize popular genres and countries producing most content
Visualization & Insights
Create bar charts, pie charts, and heatmaps
Build a Power BI dashboard for interactive exploration
5. Key Insights
Movies outnumber TV shows on Netflix, but TV shows have more frequent additions in recent years.
Popular genres include Dramas, Comedies, and Documentaries.
The United States, India, and the UK are the top content producers.
Viewer ratings show most content falls in PG, TV-MA, or TV-14 categories.
Content addition spikes in summer and year-end months, likely to capture holiday viewership.
6. Recommendations
Focus on high-performing genres in local content production.
Consider adding more family-friendly content for broader audience reach.
Use seasonal trends for marketing and content release strategies.
7. Dashboard Highlights
Genre Popularity Chart: Top 10 genres by number of titles
Content Type Over Time: Movies vs TV Shows yearly trend
Country Distribution: Heatmap of titles by production country
Rating Analysis: Average ratings by type and genre